title: NHL Player Becomes Trapped After Stick Goes Through Both Blades
text:
NHL Player Becomes Trapped After Stick Goes Through Both Blades FanDuel 12 hrs ago Daniel Utts
© FanDuel Insider
A lot of things can happen in any NHL game, but Jason Zucker of the Minnesota Wild found himself in a weird situation Thursday night. After battling with Connor Murphy and falling to the ice, he somehow found himself stuck thanks to a hockey stick between both of his skates.
AdChoices This might seem like a new strategy for a defender to use in the NHL, but it seems almost impossible to actually pull off. It took a combined effort from Murphy and Zucker. Murphy jammed his stick into the left skate of Zucker, and then while trying to get loose and back up off the ice, his right skate became stuck.
Despite Murphy’s attempt to slow down at least one player on the Wild, Minnesota found a way to win to stay undefeated on the young season.
